Sixt sees sales climbing in 1997 . German car rental company Sixt AG said on Monday it expects higher sales and a more than corresponding increase in group operating profit in 1997 . Looking ahead , the group said it expects sales to rise to four billion marks by the year 2000 and predicted a similar increase in profits . The company said in its annual report that the first quarter result for leasing and rentals had grown at a double - digit pace . In 1996 , Sixt reported sales of 2 . 11 billion marks and operating profit was 46 . 28 million marks . - - Frankfurt Newsroom + 49 69 756525 
